This repository is a throughline *source*: a requirements graph, not a program. It
re-expresses the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.2 as a grounded IDD graph
so consuming projects can compose it with throughline-compose.

WCAG 2.2 is a W3C Recommendation. The success-criterion text (each item's `text`) and the
"Intent of this Success Criterion" paragraphs (each criterion's `rationale`) are taken from:

  - Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.2 — https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/
  - Understanding WCAG 2.2 — https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG22/Understanding/
  - Canonical WCAG 2 JSON — https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG22/wcag.json

That content is © W3C and is used under the W3C Document License
(https://www.w3.org/copyright/document-license/) and the terms in
https://github.com/w3c/wcag/blob/main/11ty/json/README.md, which permit reuse with clear
attribution and without changing the content. Success-criterion text is reproduced from
the Recommendation; the principle intents and guideline rationales in this repository are
this project's own faithful summaries and are clearly additional to the W3C text.

The repository's structure, tooling and Apache-2.0 licence cover this project's own work
(the throughline graph, generator and configuration), not the underlying W3C content.
See https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/ for the authoritative source.
